<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>GOOFY GEAR UP FOR GRABS!</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/news_spiderman_2007-04-05.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Thursday, April  5, 2007</b> &mdash; Millsberry is a-buzz with rumors of a new happening in town! Mysterious water squirters have appeared in some of the city&#039;s hotspots. <i>Gazette</i> editor-in-chief Audrey Smythe-Wei went into the field herself to investigate.<br><br>A breathless Kayley Fenn was running towards her home in Westridge when she nearly collided with Audrey. <br><br>&quot;I was in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> when I spotted something moving slightly on the path,&quot; explained Kayley. &quot;I went to go pick it up and then I was covered in water and the moving thing was gone, leaving behind a propeller hat! I&#039;m on my way to tell all my friends!&quot; <br><br>Indeed, a propeller hat was perched on her head, its wings spinning slightly. Kayley continued on her way. Puzzled, Audrey went to the man who would know best&mdash;Mayor Oliver Trumble. What were these moving objects?<br>
<br>
The mayor had been preparing an official statement, and greeted Audrey with an expectant smile.  &quot;You&#039;re not mistaken,&quot; he said. &quot;We have some visitors in Millsberry. I&#039;m proud to announce the start of the Up For Grabs! Spring Challenge. Mischievous Spider-Man&trade; 3 water squirters are hiding around town. Once a day you will have the opportunity to win something when you find one!&quot;<br><br>&quot;What kind of prizes?&quot; Audrey asked excitedly.<br><br>&quot;Totally out-there goofy items!&quot; said the mayor. &quot;You&#039;ll flip when you see some of these things. Really goes along with Millsberry&#039;s April Fool&#039;s Month. And you might even win one of the four squirters themselves!&quot; <br><br>&quot;How long will this last?&quot; asked Audrey, as worked up now as Kayley had been.<br><br>&quot;The rest of this month and all of May too! You can win up to 20 prizes!&quot; With that, the mayor excused himself and got back to his work. <br><br>So, straight from the mayor&#039;s mouth, the Up For Grabs! Spring Challenge has begun, and will continue through May! Good luck spotting those squirters, and keep the spirit of April Fool&#039;s Month alive! <br></div>
